WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.859 --> 00:00:04.140
12 "First Times Ever" You Need to Know!

00:00:04.140 --> 00:00:05.520
1.

00:00:05.520 --> 00:00:08.380
The First Completed Pass ever thrown by Brett
Favre (note to Simon- pronounced “Farv”)

00:00:08.380 --> 00:00:09.380
was to himself…

00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:14.379
In his first official play in the NFL during
the second game of the 1992 season, Favre

00:00:14.379 --> 00:00:17.170
threw the ball only to have a defender deflect
it back.

00:00:17.170 --> 00:00:21.150
Favre caught the ball and was tackled for
a loss of 7 yards.

00:00:21.150 --> 00:00:22.150
2.

00:00:22.150 --> 00:00:27.900
The First Cell Phone weighed 2.4 pounds and
was 9x5x1.75 inches in size.

00:00:27.900 --> 00:00:33.090
It also had only 20 minutes of battery life
when talking, but as Motorolla employee Martin

00:00:33.090 --> 00:00:37.150
Cooper stated “that wasn’t really a big
problem because you couldn’t hold that phone

00:00:37.150 --> 00:00:38.470
up for that long.”

00:00:38.470 --> 00:00:43.810
Once the phone battery was drained, it took
approximately 10 hours to charge back up fully.

00:00:43.810 --> 00:00:44.860
3.

00:00:44.860 --> 00:00:50.710
The First UPC Barcode was a pack of Wrigley’s
Juicy Fruit gum, first scanned in Marsh’s

00:00:50.710 --> 00:00:55.420
supermarket in Troy, Ohio in June of 1974.

00:00:55.420 --> 00:00:56.420
4.

00:00:56.420 --> 00:01:01.250
The First Known Female Doctor was Merit Ptah
who lived in Egypt around 2700 B.C.

00:01:01.250 --> 00:01:05.690
According to her son who was a High Priest,
she wasn’t just any doctor, but “the Chief

00:01:05.690 --> 00:01:06.690
Physician”.

00:01:06.690 --> 00:01:07.690
5.

00:01:07.690 --> 00:01:12.470
The First Recognized “Baby Boomer” was
Kathleen Casey-Kirschling of Philadelphia.

00:01:12.470 --> 00:01:18.299
She was the first known baby to be born on
January 1, 1946, born in St. Agnes Hospital.

00:01:18.299 --> 00:01:19.299
6.

00:01:19.299 --> 00:01:23.560
The First Name In “Baskin-Robbins” was
decided by a coin-flip, with Burt Baskin winning

00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:26.860
the toss against his brother-in-law, Irv Robbins.

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:27.860
7.

00:01:27.860 --> 00:01:30.590
Man First Set Foot On The Moon at the “Sea
of Tranquility”.

00:01:30.590 --> 00:01:34.580
The second landing site was called “The
Ocean of Storms”.

00:01:34.580 --> 00:01:35.650
8.

00:01:35.650 --> 00:01:39.100
The First Punishment that will be leveled
against you if you’re convicted in the Sudan

00:01:39.100 --> 00:01:44.640
of armed robbery where you also killed someone
during the robbery (under Article 168 of the

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:47.380
Sudanese Penal Code), is that you will be
hanged.

00:01:47.380 --> 00:01:49.280
Next, you will be crucified.

00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:54.060
The last such death sentence was carried out
on May 6, 2013.

00:01:54.060 --> 00:01:55.119
9.

00:01:55.119 --> 00:01:59.681
Famed writer and Soviet spy Whittaker Chambers
was the First To Translate Bambi: A life in

00:01:59.681 --> 00:02:01.390
the Woods, into English.

00:02:01.390 --> 00:02:04.910
Disney would later, of course, base a movie
off this work.

00:02:04.910 --> 00:02:05.910
10.

00:02:05.910 --> 00:02:13.280
The First Man To Go Over Niagara Falls in
a barrel and survive, Bobby Leach, 15 years

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:17.790
later died as a result of slipping on either
an orange peel or a banana peel (different

00:02:17.790 --> 00:02:20.650
news reports from the event are contradictory
on which).

00:02:20.650 --> 00:02:24.810
After the slip and subsequent injury, his
leg became infected and had to be amputated.

00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:29.819
He died two months later from complications
from the infection and the surgery.

00:02:29.819 --> 00:02:30.819
11.

00:02:30.819 --> 00:02:36.790
Nel Blu Dipinto Di Blu, widely known as “Volare,”
was recorded by Italian singer Domenico Modugno,

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.370
and was the First Non-English Number One hit
in the history of the prestigious Billboard

00:02:40.370 --> 00:02:46.230
Hot 100 chart, when the song climbed to the
top of the American charts on August 18, 1958.

00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:50.489
It also ultimately went on to sell over 22
million copies.

00:02:50.489 --> 00:02:51.489
12.

00:02:51.489 --> 00:02:55.410
The Tower of the Winds in Athens, which lies
right under the Acropolis, is thought to be

00:02:55.410 --> 00:03:00.319
the First Clock Tower in history, constructed
sometime between the 2nd century BC to 50

00:03:00.319 --> 00:03:01.319
BC.

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:17.459
It contained eight sundials and a water clock,
along with a wind vane.

